50|$|South Korea's stance {{has drawn}} {{criticism}} from The U.N. Human Rights Committee, which argues that South Korea is violating article 18 of the ICCPR, which guarantees <b>freedom</b> <b>of</b> thought and <b>conscience.</b> In 2006, 2010, {{and again in}} 2011 the U.N. Human Rights Committee, after reviewing petitions from South Korean conscientious objectors, declared {{that the government was}} violating Article 18 of the ICCPR, the provision that guarantees the right to <b>freedom</b> <b>of</b> thought, <b>conscience</b> and religion.|$|R
